Moody's Investors Services Inc said itaffirmed the ratings on 5.3 billion dlrs of debt of GeorgiaPower Co, a unit of The Southern Co.    Affirmed were the Baa-1 first mortgage bonds, securedpollution control revenue bonds and cumulative preferred stock,and the Baa-2 unsecured pollution control revenue bonds.    Moody's said, however, that it may review the company'sdebt ratings pending a rate decision by the Georgia PublicService Commission due by October. If the rate order isunconstructive, Moody's review would have negative implicationsat that time, the agency noted. Reuter&#3;